<h2>Alternative formats — when and how</h2>

<p>Every major deliverable has at least one alternative format. The principle: <strong>same rubric, same expectations, no penalty for the choice.</strong> What changes is the medium.</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>For the Source Dossier:</strong> talk to Mr. Ignash by Block 5 if you want the video alternative.</li>
  <li><strong>For the Engineering Portfolio Defense:</strong> talk to Mr. Ignash by Block 9 if you want recorded video or written essay.</li>
  <li><strong>For block work and reflections:</strong> voice memo, video, or text — pick whichever helps you express the idea best. No pre-approval needed.</li>
</ul>

<p>If you have a reason an alternative format would help (writing anxiety, EAL, accessibility, time conflict with the defense day), say so — that's the conversation, not a special case.</p>

